In [14]:
def counts_to_probs(counts):
    counts_shots = np.sum([v for v in counts.values()])
    probs = np.zeros(2**(n), dtype=np.float64)
    for k,v in counts.items():
        probs[int(k,2)] = v/counts_shots
    return probs

def VD(p,q):
    np_p = np.array(p)
    np_q = np.array(q)
    return 0.5*np.abs(np_p - np_q).sum()

def one_itr(qc):
    qc.h(0)
    qc.cx(0,1)
    qc.barrier()
    qc.cx(0,1)
    qc.h(0)
    qc.barrier()

# Bell0 state
def pure_circuit(name=None):
    r = QuantumRegister(n)
    qc = QuantumCircuit(r, name=name)
    for it in range(itr):
        one_itr(qc)
    return r, qc  

def noise_gates_circuit(noise_params):
    angles = noise_params.reshape((3, n)) #NOT A NUMPY ARRAY FROM SCIPY.OPTIMIZE
    
    r = QuantumRegister(n)
    qc = QuantumCircuit(r)
    for it in range(itr):
        one_itr(qc)
        for q in range(n):
            qc.u(angles[0,n-q-1], angles[1,n-q-1], angles[2,n-q-1], n-q-1) # Add noise/denoise here
        qc.barrier()
    return r, qc

# Generate Circuits and Record Them
circs = []
for itr in itrs:
    print("\n\nNumber of Iterations = {:d}".format(itr))
    r, simple_qc = pure_circuit("BellStateItr{:d}".format(itr))
    simple_state = Statevector.from_instruction(simple_qc)
    # Check state
    print("Ideal State", simple_state.data)
    # Measure
    simple_qc.measure_all()
    simple_qc.draw('mpl',filename=DataFileAddress+'bell_circ_itr_{:d}_depth_{:d}.pdf'.format(itr, simple_qc.depth()))
    print("")
    # Transpile circuit
    trans_simple_qc = transpile(simple_qc, backend, initial_layout = interested_qubits, optimization_level=0)
    trans_simple_qc.draw('mpl',filename=DataFileAddress+'bell_circ_trans_itr_{:d}_depth_{:d}.pdf'.format(itr, trans_simple_qc.depth()))
    print("Original Depth = {:d}, Transpiled Depth = {:d}".format(simple_qc.depth(), trans_simple_qc.depth()))
    
    for k in range(rep):
        circs.append(trans_simple_qc.copy("BellStateItr{:d}Rep{:d}".format(itr,k)))

In [21]:
# Save Result
result_simple = job_simple.result()
counts = []
legends = []
for itr in itrs:
    itr_mems = np.array([], dtype=str)
    # Append readouts from all "rep" repeatations
    for k in range(rep):
        new_mem = result_simple.get_memory("BellStateItr{:d}Rep{:d}".format(itr,k))
        itr_mems = np.append(itr_mems, new_mem)
    # Save readouts
    np.save(DataFileAddress+'BellStateItr{:d}.npy'.format(itr),  itr_mems)
    # Record total counts
    counts.append(Counter(itr_mems))
    legends.append("Itr{:d}".format(itr))

qr = QuantumRegister(len(interested_qubits))
meas_calibs, state_labels = complete_meas_cal(qr=qr, circlabel='mcal')
for i in range(len(meas_calibs)):
    meas_calibs[i] = transpile(meas_calibs[i],backend,initial_layout=interested_qubits)

job_meas = execute(meas_calibs, backend=backend,shots=8192,optimization_level=0)
job_monitor(job_meas)

cal_results = job_meas.result()
meas_fitter = CompleteMeasFitter(cal_results,state_labels,circlabel='mcal')
meas_filter = meas_fitter.filter
